                    <li>Cooking</li>
                    <li>Heating</li>
                    <li>Entertainment</li>
                    <li>Agriculture</li>
                    <li>Construction</li>
                    <li>Production</li>
                </ul>
                How many other industries do we need to use energy - can you think of any?
            </p>
            <p>
         ");
            WriteLiteral(@"       But there are different demands placed upon these energies through different times of year
                and even different times of the day. There are also different ways in which we can capture
                energy. This lesson looks at energy usage and how we exploit energy in different ways.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- PART 1 -->
        <div class=""tab-pane fade"" id=""part1"">
            <br />
            <p><strong>Energy resources</strong></p>
            <br />
            <p>
                Energy can be used in different ways - fuels can be burnt changing chemical energy into
                heat, or kinetic energy from turning turbines that create electrical energy. But there
                are now two distinct categories of resources that we rely upon;
                <ul>
                    <li>Non-renewable energy resources</li>
                    <li>Renewable energy resources</li>
                </ul>
                Can you think what sourc");
            WriteLiteral(@"es of energy we might consider non-renewable, and which ones are
                renewable?
            </p>
        </div>

