            <p><strong>Non-renewable energy resources</strong></p>
            <br />
            <p>
                Non-renewable energy resources are sources of energy that once used, cannot be used again.
                The most common sources of energy are fossil fuels, called so because they used to be organisms
                millions and millions of years ago.
                <ul>
                    <li>Coal</li>
                    <li>Natural gas</li>
                    <li>Oil</li>
                </ul>
                Life on Earth are carbon based, meaning they have a high carbon content. Our atmosphere also has
                a high hydrogen content and due to the bonding of hydrogen and carbon, fossil fuels are often
                called 'hydrocarbons'. Wh");
            WriteLiteral(@"en burnt, these fuels release large volumes of the gas carbon dioxide
                which promotes heating of the atmosphere.
            </p>
