                </div>
            </div>
            <p>
                The two most promising renewable energy sources are <b>solar</b> and <b>wind</b> power. The Sun
                hits the planet with 430 quintillion joules of energy an hour. Solar has its obvious advantages
                and disadvantages, such as no energy at night or during poor weather but across the country,
                solar panels can still provide sufficient amounts energy during a cloudy day. Wind power is not
                very predictable or reliable, and at high wind speeds, the turbines cannot be used for fear of
                damage. They are also responsible for producing noise that disturbs flight paths for migratory
                animals, but can be implemented both on land and offshore meaning large quantities of energy can
                be create");
            WriteLiteral(@"d during the right conditions.
            </p>
